Two illustrious sons of Yobe State, Senate President Ahmed Lawan and the Minister of State for Works and Housing, Abubakar Aliyu, were on Saturday honoured by their home state. They were treated to a grand state reception by Governor Mai Mala Buni amid hundreds of supporters at the Banquet Hall of Government House, Damaturu. While Senator Lawan was honoured for his election as the President of the ninth Senate of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, Aliyu was honoured for his appointment as a minister. Aliyu is the immediate past deputy governor of the state.